

3 ways to add CSS code into HTML:

	a. embedded into the tag  -- css only apply to this element

		<h2 style="color:Tomato;">Enough evidence uncovered to indict Trump</h2>

	b. use class: -- all elements could use this class

		<style>
		    .learnFromYahoo {
		        color:Tomato;
		    }
		</style>

		<h2 class="learnFromYahoo">Enough evidence uncovered to indict Trump</h2>

	c. use defined-tag:  -- all element with the same tag the css will apply

		<style>
		    h2 {
		        color:Tomato;
		    }
		</style>
		
		<h2>Enough evidence uncovered to indict Trump</h2>
		<h2>Hi alan again</h2>
